canonical:
  title: 寄妻兄閔及菴
  author: 白彌堅
  language: lzh
  text: 笛聲江郡落梅花西望長安日已斜栗里舊居楊柳在不知春色屬誰家
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 寄妻兄閔及菴
  author: 白彌堅
  language: lzh
  text: 笛聲江郡落梅花。西望長安日已斜。栗里舊居楊柳在。不知春色屬誰家。
korean:
  title: 기처형민급암
  author: 백미견
  language: kor
  text: |-
    피리 소리 강 고을에 매화꽃이 지는데
    서편으로 장안을 바라보매 해가 이미 기우네
    율리의 옛 집에는 버들 아직 있건마는
    알 수 없어라 봄빛은 누구 집에 붙였는고
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_0390&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 율리(栗里)의 …… 있건마는 : '
    value: 도연명(陶淵明)이 율리(栗里)에 은거(隱居)하면서 문 앞에 버드나무 다섯 그루를 심었다.
english:
  title: A Letter to My Wife's Elder Brother, Min Geubam
  author: Baek Mi-gyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A flute's song drifts through the river town as plum blossoms fall.
    Gazing westward toward Chang'an, the sun already slopes low.
    At Yuli's ancient dwelling, willows still stand—
    Yet who can say to which house spring's hue belongs?
  footnotes:
    - 'Yuli (栗里): The retreat of the Eastern Jin poet Tao Yuanming (陶淵明), who famously planted five willows before his cottage door and took the name ''Five Willows'' as a symbol of his reclusive life.'
    - 'Chang''an: The ancient capital, here evoking nostalgia and perhaps the poet''s distance from home or center of power.'
